<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><channel><title>Music on Mike Letts</title><link>https://michaelthomasletts.com/tags/music/</link><description>Recent content in Music on Mike Letts</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><managingEditor>lettsmt@gmail.com (Mike Letts)</managingEditor><webMaster>lettsmt@gmail.com (Mike Letts)</webMaster><copyright>© Copyright 2026, Michael (Mike) Letts</copyright><lastBuildDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 23:31:24 -0500</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://michaelthomasletts.com/tags/music/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Some miscellaneous songs and albums which are unavailable on Spotify</title><link>https://michaelthomasletts.com/blog/misc-music/</link><pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 23:31:24 -0500</pubDate><author>lettsmt@gmail.com (Mike Letts)</author><guid>https://michaelthomasletts.com/blog/misc-music/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;I recently shared a link to my Spotify account on my website, as I&amp;rsquo;m sure you noticed in the navigation bar. It dawned on me afterwards that Spotify is missing many of my favorite songs and albums - most of my Spotify playlists feel like incomplete representations of my taste as a result - so I thought to share some miscellaneous favorites with you all which, to the best of my knowledge, aren&amp;rsquo;t available on Spotify.&lt;/p&gt;</description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I recently shared a link to my Spotify account on my website, as I&rsquo;m sure you noticed in the navigation bar. It dawned on me afterwards that Spotify is missing many of my favorite songs and albums - most of my Spotify playlists feel like incomplete representations of my taste as a result - so I thought to share some miscellaneous favorites with you all which, to the best of my knowledge, aren&rsquo;t available on Spotify.</p>
<p>I previously worked at Spotify as a contractor, as many of you know, but, as somebody who initially attended university with intentions to become an artist, I have some mixed thoughts and feelings about the company. Maybe I will share my thoughts on how Spotify has shaped the music industry and artist&rsquo;s careers some other time, or maybe I&rsquo;ll share more about why I decided not to pursue a creative career . . .</p>
<p>For now, however, I hope you all find something you like below.</p>
